  "prompt": "Why do I still love him?",
  "response": "It's completely natural to have lingering feelings for someone even after a relationship has ended. Love is a complex emotion that doesn't simply vanish when circumstances change. There could be several reasons why you might still have strong feelings for him:\n\n1. **Emotional attachment**: Shared experiences and emotional bonds can create a deep sense of attachment that isn't easily broken.\n\n2. **Memories**: Positive and cherished memories can make it hard to let go.\n\n3. **Unresolved feelings**: If the relationship ended abruptly or without closure, you might still have unresolved emotions.\n\n4. **Personal growth**: Sometimes, reflecting on past relationships can be part of your growth process, helping you understand yourself better.\n\n5. **Hope for the future**: You might still harbor hope for reconciliation or wonder about what might have been.\n\nIt's important to give yourself time and space to process these feelings. Talking to friends, family, or a therapist can provide support and guidance as you navigate this challenging time.",
